18/07/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Parliament adopted a law Monday (17 July), envisioning the establishment of a national anti-corruption council by the end of October. Four members of the council will be selected by parliament; the rest will represent NGOs, media, employers, trade unions and the academic community. The council is to monitor public institutions to prevent corrupt practices, review complaints and submit annual reports to parliament. (Poslovni dnevnik - 18/07/06)
